  "body": "**Describe the bug**\r\nOn My sepolia-prysm node I observed, that during OldHeaders downloading, Snap and State were executed.\r\nSeems like some peers were reassigned to snap and then never returned back and node \"stucked\" on \r\nOld Headers 1608576 / 2785000\r\nhttps://seq.nethermind.io/#/events?filter=Contains(NodeName,%20'Smoke-Tests-Masterv202062023-sepolia-p')%20and%20not%20%22Big%20Snappy%20message%22%20and%20not%20%22DEBUG%2FERROR%22and%20not%20%22Attempt%20to%20request%20ENR%20before%20bonding%22%20and%20not%20%22when%20synchronizing%20(Timeout)%22%20and%20not%20%20%22free%20disk%20space%22\r\n\r\nNoticed from this screen that all peers after few minutes were reassigned from headers/Snap to Nodes only:\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/43241881/217276348-83d18e4e-f45c-48ea-90f6-615a3f8e5c6e.png)\r\n\r\nAnd moving forward all peers we are connected with are not serving anything (all brackets are empty like below):\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/43241881/217276688-cfe346b5-3925-41b0-99fd-18695c33be41.png)\r\n\r\n",
